==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tralatitious
<hw>Tral`a*ti"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tralatitius</ets>, <ets>translatitius</ets>,
<ets>tralaticius</ets>, <ets>translaticius</ets>. See
<er>Tralation</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Passed along; handed down;
transmitted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Among biblical critics a <qex>tralatitious</qex> interpretation is
one received by expositor from expositor.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Withington.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Metaphorical; figurative; not literal.</def>
<rj><au>Stackhouse.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tralatitiously</ent>⟦br⟧
